Question,Answer
What is kubectl?,kubectl is the command-line tool used to interact with a Kubernetes cluster.
What caused the "Exec format error" when installing kubectl?,You downloaded the wrong CPU architecture binary (amd64 instead of ARM64 for your VM).
Why did kubectl first show "Permission denied"?,Because the binary was not marked as executable (missing chmod +x).
What is the correct kubectl installation step sequence?,Download binary → chmod +x → move to /usr/local/bin → verify.
Why did sudo kubectl fail in k3d setup?,Because sudo uses root which does not have the kubeconfig configured.
What is kubeconfig?,A configuration file that tells kubectl which cluster to connect to and how.
What does k3d do?,k3d runs lightweight Kubernetes clusters (k3s) inside Docker containers.
What is required before using k3d?,A working Docker installation.
What happened when k3d cluster create succeeded?,It created a full Kubernetes cluster running inside Docker containers.
Why did kubectl show localhost:8080 error?,Because it had no valid kubeconfig and defaulted to a non-existent local cluster.
What fixes kubectl not connecting to k3d cluster?,Setting KUBECONFIG to the k3d-generated config file.
What is a Kubernetes namespace?,A logical partition inside a cluster used to organize and isolate resources.
Can multiple environments exist in one Kubernetes cluster?,Yes, dev, staging, and prod can all run in one cluster using namespaces.
What is the benefit of namespaces?,They provide organization, isolation, name separation, and resource control.
What happens if you do not use namespaces?,Everything goes into the default namespace, causing clutter and no separation.
Are namespaces full security boundaries?,No, they are soft isolation; real security is handled by RBAC.
What is RBAC in Kubernetes?,Role-Based Access Control that defines what actions users can perform.
What is Argo CD?,A GitOps tool that continuously syncs Kubernetes state with Git repositories.
Is Argo CD a microservices system?,Yes, it is made of multiple containerized components working together.
What are main Argo CD components?,argocd-server, repo-server, application-controller, dex-server, and Redis.
Why does Argo CD use a namespace?,To isolate system components from user applications and simplify management.
What happens if Argo CD is installed without a namespace?,All its components go into the default namespace, causing clutter and poor organization.
What is kubectl apply -n argocd -f doing?,It installs all Argo CD resources into the argocd namespace.
What does kubectl get pods -n argocd do?,It lists only the pods inside the argocd namespace.
Why use namespaces in Kubernetes?,To organize resources and separate environments within the same cluster.
What is the relationship between kubectl, k3d, and Kubernetes?,kubectl is the client, k3d creates the cluster, Kubernetes runs the system.
